{"type":"message","id":"31fb8848","parentId":"ed2d4a7d","timestamp":"2026-06-05T08:06:33.369Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see something very interesting! PH prices are clearly in PHP (Philippine Pesos), and there are some very high-priced items. But the unit is $199 PHP, which is about $3.50 USD. So the prices are actually quite reasonable in USD terms.\n\nBut wait - the user is selling in Vietnam and Thailand, not Philippines. So these PH prices don't directly help unless they're also selling in PH.\n\nLet me refocus. The user's market is VN and TH. For these markets:\n- VN Hair Clips avg $1.11 (in VND terms) - too low\n- VN Headbands growth +60% but avg $1.46 - too low\n\n\n- TH sites weren't returning data\n\nThe real issue is that these developing markets just have inherently low price points for hair accessories. MY has better pricing at $4-7.50 but is declining, while VN and TH are stuck at rock-bottom prices with minimal margin potential. I'm wondering if the approach should shift entirely - instead of chasing cheap accessories in low-tier markets, maybe I should be looking at higher-margin product categories altogether.\n\nLet me test whether TH and GB sites actually work with the category search, and if so, what kind of pricing I can find there. The API was returning errors earlier, so there's a possibility some sites just don't have accessible data.\n","thinkingSignature":"c2ee86e6cd69d7a6f256118e9d9968206352ca9c34dd86f7126175595f57517f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_f3aca4a2f72241dfab0b940f","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/halei/workspace-tts && \\\necho \"=== 测试 TH 泰国 ===\" && \\\nmcporter call sorftime-mcp.tiktok_category_name_search searchName=\"hair clip\" site=TH --output json 2>&1 && \\\necho \"\" && echo \"=== 测试 GB 英国 ===\" && \\\nmcporter call sorftime-mcp.tiktok_category_name_search searchName=\"hair clip\" site=GB --output json 2>&1 && \\\necho \"\" && echo \"=== 测试 US 美国 ===\" 