{"type":"message","id":"3276c8ab","parentId":"c4fb8d30","timestamp":"2026-06-05T08:14:55.443Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying: \"These all need to be scanned - they're all in the hair accessories category: headbands, hair clips, hair pins, hair ties.\"\n\nAnd: \"My goal is high quality, high profit. Can't you scan the data types and formats provided by the Sorftime MCP?\"\n\nThe user wants me to look at what Sorftime MCP actually provides - what data types and fields are available from the various tools. They want to understand what filters can be applied at the Sorftime level vs what we need to filter ourselves.\n\nLet me read the Sorftime skill to understand what tools/fields are actually available.\n\nActually, the user seems to be saying: don't blame Sorftime, look at what data it actually provides and use that properly to filter for high-quality/high-profit products. \n\nSo they're asking me to check the actual Sorftime MCP schema to see what filtering capabilities we have at the source.\n","thinkingSignature":"b99ab0ad45531c3d09ae055d14a7438fc1b420ff1e048957e1fb936074168cb1"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n明白，你说得对。让我看看 Sorftime MCP 实际返回了哪些字段和数据类型，然后找出能直接筛高价品的方法。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_e598d34b315745f9a68642d9","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/halei/workspace-tts && cat .openclaw/mcp_configs/sorftime-mcp.json 2>/dev/null || cat ~/.openclaw/mcp_configs/sorftime-mcp.json 2>/dev/null || echo \"not found\""}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_d0edc5b939b14907815ffab0","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls ~/.openclaw/mcp_configs/ 2>/dev/null || echo \"no mcp_configs dir\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54996,"output":326,"cacheRead":8535,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":63857,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780645976751,"responseId":"0671b359cc28c5b7f67da1b3