{"type":"message","id":"0a2122bc","parentId":"abfdb4d9","timestamp":"2026-06-05T08:14:55.447Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Even a minimal update with empty property fails. This suggests the API might have a different update endpoint or structure for bitable fields. Let me try using the feishu_bitable_app_table action with a patch instead, or maybe I need to use the drive API.\n\nActually, wait - maybe the issue is that I should be using the app token in a different way, or maybe the field_id format is wrong. Let me check if the field list action returned the correct field_id.\n\nActually, looking at the data again, the field_id is `fldSTvlEVK`. Let me try calling the API directly with curl to see what error we get.\n\nActually, let me try a completely different approach. \n\nSince I can't update the field options, I could create a new SingleSelect field for站点 (site) with MY as an option, but that would create duplicate columns. The existing \"站点\" field only has Thailand, Vietnam, and VN options, so the simplest solution is probably to just manually add \"马来西亚\" or \"MY\" as a new option directly in the Feishu interface, since the API update keeps failing.\n\nAlternatively, I could add \"MY\" or \"马来西亚\" as a text value when writing records - Feishu SingleSelect fields allow adding new options dynamically when you write a value that doesn't exist yet. But ideally I'd fix the field properly. Let me try creating a completely new field to see if that works, or check if the issue is with the app_token format or some other parameter I'm missing.\n","thinkingSignature":"a73dd6c4a15668abf6265344a69fcb3a64c6dffa99a91dc71a130d65c5b66ddc"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_281d7e032a79496d9fce7040","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 直接调飞书API看看更新字段的真正错误\nAPP_TOKEN=\"AKppbA…QnZd\"\nTABLE_ID=\"tblHU2do30jzinJT\"\nFIELD_ID=\"fldSTvlEVK\"\n\n# 先获取tenant_access_token\nTOKEN_RESP=$(curl -s -X POST \"https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/auth/v